Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Insurance to the
original bill:
1. Remove the Cash Bail Fund Surety and GPS Monitoring Provider Licensure
provisions.
2. Remove proposed law relative to electronic monitoring providers from Title 22
to Title 15 of the La. Revised Statutes.
3. Proposed law provisions relative to electronic monitoring providers provide for:
definitions, registration, maintenance, certification requirements, and required
disclosures.
4. Authorize the Louisiana Commission on Law Enforcement and Administration
of Criminal Justice to enforce compliance and maintain the registration status of
electronic monitoring providers.
